args: (He said they were heading north again,\nand I've found myself along with them.)
(So what do I do? I mean, telling them\nI was making up rupie magic after all\nthey did for me is just so...awkward.)
Nina? You're sort of staring off into space.\nEverything okay?
Huh? Oh yeah, I'm good! I can fight!
(Okay. For now, I just need to fight\nand prove that I won't be a burden.)
Impressive stuff, ladyâ€”but I bet that's\njust the beginning for you, huh?
Yeah, let's see that beefed-up rupie magic!
(They're all expecting it, so I need to make\nit look like the magic got powered up.)
(I REALLY wish I hadn't said all that stuff\nabout it getting stronger the more you\nearn, but there's nothing for it now.)
Whoooa! You mopped up that bunch\nof fiends before I could blink!
Uh, well...it's all because of the extra\npower you helped me earn!
Look lively, everybody! This one's no joke.
Aw, we've got nothing to worry about\nwith Nina the Killer on our side!
No lies there. Now go give 'em\nthe ol' rupie razzle, Nina!
The ol'...rupie razzle... Uh, right! Haaah!
(Shoot! I need to squeeze more power\nout of my magical device!)
Oh man! It looks like whatever Nina\nwas holding there just blew up!
It exploded while she was tryin'\nto gather up mana!
Hang on. Nina, did all of your magic\nactually come from that device?
That fiend was ten pounds'a angry in a\ntwo-pound sack, but we managed to\ntake it out.
Good. But, um, did your magic actually\ncome from that thing you were holding\nearlier? The one that blew up?
Yeah, it did. And before you ask, also yes.\nI...I made up rupie magic.
But why would you make up\nsomething like that?!
Because I wanted to join up with you!
But I thought you'd tell me I'd just be in\nthe way because I couldn't fight, so...
Why were you so determined to join us?
Because it's my dreamâ€”one I inherited\nfrom my dad along with the shop.
See, Dad was born in North Grastaea,\nbut the ravages of war drove him south.
He'd always dreamed of opening a shop\nin his hometown, and I wanted to make it\nhappen. For him, you know?
That explains your fixation on the north.
Yep. So when I heard what you were doing\nup there, it gave me an idea.
I figured if I could hitch a ride up there\nwith you guys, I might finally be able to\nput Dad's plan into motion.
And it worked! I was able to make some\nprofessional connections in Valzgald,\nwhich was his hometown.
One thing led to another, and eventually\nI took ownership of an empty storefront.
Sounds like your dream is pretty close\nto becoming a reality.
Yeahâ€”and thanks to Luca and Ranzal and\nall the rest of you, I earned enough money\nto actually open the second store!
I've wanted to apologize for tricking youâ€”\nI really, REALLY didâ€”but I just couldn't\nfind a way to say it. I'm really sorry.

But you didn't trick us, Nina! I mean,
sure, your power came from somewhere
else, but it was still power, and we owed
you that debt fair and square.
Ain't no skin off my nose helping a friend\nfulfill a dream.
Thank you both. I don't think you'll ever\nknow how much you did for me.
I couldn't have said it better, Nina.\nAnd congrats on your grand opening!

Oh, and by way of apology, please let me
stick with you all for a little longer! Once I
fix up my magic device, I'll be able to help
you all out again.
I'm sorry, Nina, but we can't do that.
Even if you do fix your magical tool,\nwhat if it blows up again? You'd be in\nserious danger if that ever happened.
Um, well... Yeah, I guess I don't really\nhave anything I can say to that.
I'm glad you understand. And with that,\nwe need to get going.
We'll keep you protected until we get back\nto Alberia, so don't worry about a thing.
R-right. Sure. Sorry for the trouble...
(It's like I just ended up using all of them\nfor the sake of my dream.)
(And sure, they forgave me, but I still feel\njust awful about everything...)
